Genitalia (
Fig. 3C
) of Brunner’s 
type
A (
Brunner von Wattenwyl 1888
). Tergite VIII not modified compared to preceding tergites. Tergite IX not extended; end of tergite bent backwards/downwards, with a minute median emargination on posterior margin.Appendices cerciferae base enclaved between tergite IX lateral lobes and tergite end; appendices cerciferae with a process forming a long coiled spur with an acute apex, the spur bent at the base; on dead specimens, both appendices cerciferae processes lying head-to-tail, side by side; length and angle of process bent variable within the species without discrete classes. SGP with a shallow emargination (
Fig. 2H
); styli not thickened (length: 1.35 ± 
0.02 mm
).

Sternite before SGP (
VII
): bearing a long process on sternite anterior margin, directed backwards; reaching usually SGP base (depending on stuffing); process base weakly sclerotized, flat; process apex ladle-shaped with the concavity directed ventrally (the curvature depends on the preservation), the dorsal part strongly sclerotized.
